In this article, President Trump offers condolences to the people of El Paso, Texas, and Dayton, Ohio, following the recent mass shootings in those cities. He praises the law enforcement in both places for their quick response and actions. The President also emphasizes that hate has no place in the country and that efforts will be made to address the issue. He mentions speaking with Attorney General Bill Barr, FBI Director Christopher Wray, governors, and members of Congress to discuss potential actions. President Trump states that a statement will be made the following day at 10 o'clock. When asked about addressing the issue of gun control, he mentions ongoing discussions and efforts, highlighting that mental illness is also a significant factor. The article concludes with the President expressing gratitude and stating that more needs to be done to tackle the problem.